	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />You don't even need to mod the expansion port; a simple jumper pack that connects the output and input pins (plus any caps/resistors) is all you'd need. There's evidence that Nintendo planned to do this with the MMC5. As I recall, though, the main problem with that option is finding/making a connector that'll fit the NES's oddball expansion slot.

		

